{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.48",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 48,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 48 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:1",
      "text": "Great is the Lord and greatly to be praised in the city of our God! His holy mountain,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:2",
      "text": "beautiful in elevation, is the joy of all the earth, Mount Zion, in the far north, the city of the great King.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:3",
      "text": "Within her citadels God has shown himself a sure defense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:4",
      "text": "For lo, the kings assembled, they came on together.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:5",
      "text": "As soon as they saw it, they were astounded, they were in panic, they took to flight;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:6",
      "text": "trembling took hold of them there, anguish as of a woman in travail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:7",
      "text": "By the east wind thou didst shatter the ships of Tarshish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:8",
      "text": "As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of the Lord of hosts, in the city of our God, which God establishes for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:9",
      "text": "We have thought on thy steadfast love, O God, in the midst of thy temple.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:10",
      "text": "As thy name, O God, so thy praise reaches to the ends of the earth. Thy right hand is filled with victory;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:11",
      "text": "let Mount Zion be glad! Let the daughters of Judah rejoice because of thy judgments!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:12",
      "text": "Walk about Zion, go round about her, number her towers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:13",
      "text": "consider well her ramparts, go through her citadels; that you may tell the next generation",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.48.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 48,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 48:14",
      "text": "that this is God, our God for ever and ever. He will be our guide for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
